name: Civet Coffee
description: Cruetly Free and Foraged Civet Coffee from the plantations of Western Ghats of Karnataka, India. "Kopi Luwak" the Indonesian word for Civet Coffee, is the world's most expensive coffee. With origins in Indonesian island of Sumatra, Civet Coffee has spread around the World. Ainmane is the first to bring to you from the coffee plantations of Coorg. Relish a cup and find out why the Civet picks the best cherries and make it a brew to remember.

name: Skandapuri Estate - Arabica
description: Skandapuri-Magarat Estate located at the Modur Village is situated at an elevation of 3200ft close to Madikeri, Coorg. These arabica beans tend to have a sweeter & softer profile with tones of citrus fruits and sharp acidity. Ainmane has exclusive access to this plantation to witness the lifecycle of the beans being grown and harvested. This bag of single origin beans is completely based on the 'Crop to Cup' concept.
